text.tspan: Our goal is to educate the population of both
migrant and native-born American youth and
their parents in an effort to reduce the stressors
experienced by adolescent migrants in the
United States and eliminate the overall stigma
Studies regarding the mental health of the
youth migrant population show that stress is
one of the most dominant factors affecting
health. Wam aims to unite and educate a
community of people and provide them with
the resources needed to lead happy and
healthy lives in their new home.
